WEBVTT

00:04.528 --> 00:06.779
What the heck is kohlrabi?

00:06.813 --> 00:08.147
It's a German turnip.

00:08.180 --> 00:09.899
Does it taste good?

00:09.950 --> 00:12.201
It's a German turnip.

00:12.235 --> 00:13.736
(Sighs)

00:13.787 --> 00:17.623
Daikon? Uh, komatsuna?
This is why I miss Iowa.

00:17.658 --> 00:18.874
People ate normal things

00:18.909 --> 00:21.026
like potatoes and corn
and lard.

00:21.044 --> 00:22.962
Again, just a dinner party.

00:22.996 --> 00:25.047
You're not required to serve
gourmet food.

00:25.082 --> 00:27.049
But these are our friends
from the country club.

00:27.084 --> 00:29.835
I want to impress them.
I want to impress Michael.

00:29.869 --> 00:31.170
Oh, you don't have to worry
about that.

00:31.204 --> 00:32.838
He's crazy about you.

00:32.872 --> 00:34.557
He is, isn't he?

00:34.591 --> 00:36.392
Okay.
Let's go with the jicama.

00:36.426 --> 00:38.678
I think I've heard of that one.

00:38.712 --> 00:40.045
(Chuckles)

00:40.063 --> 00:43.015
So for dessert, what do you...

00:45.435 --> 00:46.719
(Lowered voice)
Is that Olivia?

00:46.737 --> 00:48.104
(Lowered voice)
What am I gonna do?

00:48.155 --> 00:50.690
- Relax. She hasn't seen us yet.
- Okay.

00:50.724 --> 00:51.824
Oh!

00:51.858 --> 00:54.560
(Clattering)

00:54.578 --> 00:56.912
<i>And now she has.</i>

00:59.232 --> 01:00.666
(Lowered voice)
Why is she coming over here?

01:00.701 --> 01:02.668
(Lowered voice) It's okay.
I got your back.

01:02.703 --> 01:05.705
Marisol,
I thought that was you.

01:05.739 --> 01:07.072
Hello, Olivia.

01:07.090 --> 01:08.874
I don't mean to interrupt,

01:08.908 --> 01:10.176
but I've been wanting
to talk to you.

01:10.210 --> 01:12.044
I feel I owe you an apology.

01:12.078 --> 01:13.596
An apology?

01:13.630 --> 01:15.297
I was so rude the other day.

01:15.348 --> 01:17.600
I don't blame you for throwing
me out of Michael's house.

01:17.634 --> 01:19.185
I deserved it.

01:19.219 --> 01:21.587
Wow.

01:21.605 --> 01:24.023
I'm really not a bad person,
Marisol.

01:24.057 --> 01:26.192
I wish you could've known me
before the divorce,

01:26.226 --> 01:28.778
back when I was happy.

01:28.812 --> 01:31.697
Anyway, I hope you can
forgive me.

01:31.732 --> 01:33.065
Sure I can,

01:33.099 --> 01:35.818
but it was Taylor's party
that you ruined.

01:35.869 --> 01:39.739
You should apologize to her.

01:39.773 --> 01:41.123
Oh.

01:41.158 --> 01:43.826
See, here's the problem.

01:43.877 --> 01:46.712
I don't apologize to whores.

01:46.747 --> 01:48.881
And I'm not speaking
metaphorically

01:48.915 --> 01:50.332
when I use that word.

01:50.383 --> 01:52.284
She's an actual whore.
Men used to pay her for sex.

01:52.302 --> 01:54.953
In fact,
that's how she met Michael.

01:54.971 --> 01:57.006
Oh, was that a secret?

01:57.057 --> 01:59.141
Oops.

